Key Match Events: Jrue Holiday scored 12 points in the first quarter and had a strong overall performance with 39 points, 15 assists, and 6 steals. The Celtics' defense was effective, limiting the Rockets to 36.4% shooting and 9 assists, the fewest in nearly three years. Kristaps Porzingis' return helped clog the paint, contributing to the Celtics' 30-point second half and limiting the Rockets to 30 points in the paint, 21.9 below their season average.
Post-Match Reflections: Head Coach Mazzulla praised Jrue Holiday's aggressiveness and hustle, noting his impact on the defensive end. Mazzulla also highlighted Kristaps Porzingis's strong defensive performance in his return from injury.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Celtics are 17-2 this season and 46-2 all-time when Jrue Holiday scores in double digits. The team aims to be fully healthy soon with Jaylen Brown's expected return from a shoulder injury to face the Oklahoma City Thunder, winners of 14 straight.
